}I . upwelling blooms off the coast of Africa, parallels the strength and extent of the Ekman surface drift. Upwelling, when broadly defined to include large scale vertical excursions of the thermocline, explains virtually all of the surface chlorophyll observations in excess of 0.5 mg m-3, except in the river plumes.},
